u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/b0/b0aa7ad2b4be56ddf53621df2997358d.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x685\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/b0/b0aa7ad2b4be56ddf53621df2997358d.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/b0/b0aa7ad2b4be56ddf53621df2997358d.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/b0/b0aa7ad2b4be56ddf53621df2997358d.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/b0/b0aa7ad2b4be56ddf53621df2997358d.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage credit: Takeru Koroda\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eBlending with its rural surroundings, the exterior employs local materials and finishes, including black plaster walls referencing Naoshima’s traditional burned-cedar facades and pebble walls inspired by vernacular architecture in the nearby Honmura district. The building’s sweeping roofline echoes the contours of the surrounding hills, designed to embed the structure into the landscape.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/33/33c202779688a4b0b78b706bff94de6c.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x685\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/33/33c202779688a4b0b78b706bff94de6c.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/33/33c202779688a4b0b78b706bff94de6c.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/33/33c202779688a4b0b78b706bff94de6c.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/33/33c202779688a4b0b78b706bff94de6c.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage credit: Takeru Koroda\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/1b/1ba3ac4328a14fd119ebc2ca49a5e14e.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x770\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/1b/1ba3ac4328a14fd119ebc2ca49a5e14e.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/1b/1ba3ac4328a14fd119ebc2ca49a5e14e.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/1b/1ba3ac4328a14fd119ebc2ca49a5e14e.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/1b/1ba3ac4328a14fd119ebc2ca49a5e14e.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage credit: GION\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eA cafe on the north side of the ground floor opens onto a terrace with panoramic views of the Seto Inland Sea, including sights of Teshima and local fishing boats. The public amenities are part of an effort to frame the museum as more than an exhibition space, but as a gathering place for locals and visitors.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/2a/2a0f4a43c22eb20207e63b16561812f8.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x685\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/2a/2a0f4a43c22eb20207e63b16561812f8.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/2a/2a0f4a43c22eb20207e63b16561812f8.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/2a/2a0f4a43c22eb20207e63b16561812f8.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/2a/2a0f4a43c22eb20207e63b16561812f8.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage credit: GION\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/32/32f59557fe927b993c564e6ac1e8f5c7.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x685\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/32/32f59557fe927b993c564e6ac1e8f5c7.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/32/32f59557fe927b993c564e6ac1e8f5c7.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/32/32f59557fe927b993c564e6ac1e8f5c7.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/32/32f59557fe927b993c564e6ac1e8f5c7.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage credit: Takeru Koroda\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003e“It is my belief that the experiences in Naoshima will forever linger in the memories of those who visit the island,” Ando said about the project. “The songs we listened to and the works of art we saw in our childhood are never forgotten. I hope that many children will visit Naoshima and be able to feel their senses being stimulated so that they can open up doors to a new world.”\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e“Such “moving experiences” have the power to nourish human beings and refine our senses that will in turn lead to more opportunities to be emotionally moved,” Ando added. “Naoshima is an island like no other that is filled with such opportunities. For the Naoshima New Museum of Art, I once again endeavored to build a place that cultivates sensibilities and moves people’s hearts.”\u003c/p\u003e\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cbr clear=\"all\"/\u003e\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ca name=\"comments\" id=\"CommentsAnchor\"\u003e \u003c/a\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/ul\u003e\n\t  \t\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
